                           <children>
                              <TextArea editable="false" prefHeight="378.0" prefWidth="467.0" text="                                                          PRACTICE&#10;&#10;In practice mode, you willl be inputting a number between 1 and 99 inclusive. &#10;The number will then be displayed, and you will need to record yourself saying&#10;the number out in Te Reo Maori, by pressing the Record button. You can hear&#10;your recording by pressing the Play Back button. You can re-record by pressing&#10;the Record button again. You can re-record and re-play your recording as many&#10;times as you wish. Once you are satisfied, you can press the Check button to&#10;checkif you got the number right. You will be given feedback based on what the&#10;system heard.&#10;&#10;In this mode, no stats are recorded." AnchorPane.bottomAnchor="5.0" AnchorPane.leftAnchor="5.0" AnchorPane.rightAnchor="5.0" AnchorPane.topAnchor="5.0" />
                           </children>
                        </AnchorPane>
                  </content>
                </Tab>
                <Tab text="Pronunciation">
                  <content>
                    <AnchorPane minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0" prefHeight="180.0" prefWidth="200.0">
                           <children>
                              <TextArea editable="false" prefHeight="378.0" prefWidth="467.0" text="                                      LEVELS 1 AND 2:  PRONUNCIATION&#10;&#10;In these levels, you are given a number, from 1 - 9 inclusive (in Level 1) or 1 - 99&#10;inclusive (in Level 2). You can skip the number and see the correct answer,or you &#10;can press the Record button, to record yourself saying the number out in Te Reo&#10;Maori. You will be able to hear your recording by pressing the Play Back button,&#10;or you can re-record the recording by pressing the Record button again. You can&#10;re-play and re-record the recording as many times as you want, prior to &#10;submission.&#10;&#10;Once you are happy, you can press the Check button to check whether or not &#10;your answer was correct. You will be given feedback based on what the system&#10;heard. If you got the answer wrong, you are given a second chance to record it,&#10;after which you will see the correct answer, if you get it wrong again. &#10;&#10;Once you finish the level, you are given your score. There are 10 questions in this&#10;level. If you score 8 or more, you will unlock the next level. In either case, you are&#10;given the option to retry the level.&#10;&#10;Good luck!&#10;" AnchorPane.bottomAnchor="5.0" AnchorPane.leftAnchor="5.0" AnchorPane.rightAnchor="5.0" AnchorPane.topAnchor="5.0" />
                           </children></AnchorPane>
                  </content>
                </Tab>
                  <Tab text="Math Easy">
                    <content>
                      <AnchorPane minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0" prefHeight="180.0" prefWidth="200.0">
                           <children>
                              <TextArea editable="false" prefHeight="378.0" prefWidth="467.0" text="                                               LEVEL 3: ARITHMETIC&#10;&#10;In this level, we will be introducing the &quot;math&quot; aspect of the game. An expression &#10;will be displayed, which will always evaluate to a number between 1 and 99 &#10;inclusive. You can skip the question an, see the correct answer or you canpress&#10;the Record button and record yourself saying what you believe the expression &#10;evaluates to in Te Reo Maori . You will then be given the choice to hear the&#10;recording, by pressing the Play Back button. You can re-record and re-play the&#10;recording as many times until you are satisfied.&#10;&#10;Once you are happy, you will need to press the Check button, and you will be &#10;given feedback on whether or not your last answer was correct, based on what &#10;the machine heard. If you are correct, then you can move on to the next question,&#10;and if not, you are given a second chance, after which you will see the correct &#10;answer.&#10;&#10;The total number of questions is 15. If you score 12 or more, you can advance &#10;to the next level. In either case, you are given the option of repeating this level.&#10;&#10;Good luck!&#10;" AnchorPane.bottomAnchor="5.0" AnchorPane.leftAnchor="5.0" AnchorPane.rightAnchor="5.0" AnchorPane.topAnchor="5.0" />
                           </children>
                        </AnchorPane>
