                           <children>
                              <TextArea editable="false" prefHeight="378.0" prefWidth="467.0" text="                                            LEVEL 5: ADVANCED MATHS&#10;&#10;WARNING!!!! THIS LEVEL IS INTENDED FOR PEOPLE WITH A GOOD BACKGROUND &#10;IN MATHEMATICS TO CHALLENGE THEIR MATHEMATICAL SKILLS WHILE &#10;PRACTICING TE REO MAORI. IF YOU HAVE MATHEMATICAL ANXIETY OR &#10;ANY RELATED CONDITION, DO NOT PROCEED BEYOND LEVEL 3.&#10;&#10;This level is designed to really test your mathematical skills and knowledge. Based&#10;on the NCEA Level 3 course of the New Zealand curriculum, this level will&#10;challenge those of you who have excelled in high school mathematics. As before,&#10;a math problem will be displayed. What the question requires will be displayed&#10;on the question, but there will always be exactly ONE answer between 1 and 99 &#10;inclusive. You are to record, yourself saying that number in Te Reo Maori. The &#10;rest is all the same as the previous levels.&#10;&#10;The total number of questions in this level is 20. &#10;&#10;Good luck!" />
